==== Phase 8: Testing & Validation ====

Comprehensive testing checklist:

Test 1: DNS Resolution

nslookup [service].lab.local
# Should resolve to correct IP

ping [service].lab.local
# Should respond

Test 2: Service Accessibility

# From browser:
http://[service].lab.local
# Should load service UI

# From command line:
curl -I http://[service].lab.local
# Should return HTTP 200

Test 3: Basic Functionality

# Perform core service function:
# - Create test account
# - Upload test file
# - Run test query
# - Whatever the service's primary function is

Test 4: Data Persistence

# Create test data in service

# Restart service:
ssh [user]@[target-vm]
docker compose restart [service]

# Verify test data still exists
# This confirms volume mounts are correct

Test 5: Full Container Restart

docker compose stop [service]
docker compose up -d [service]

# Verify service starts cleanly
docker logs [service]
# Should show no errors

# Verify data persists

Test 6: Access from Different Clients

# Test from:
# - Your laptop
# - Another VM
# - Phone (via VPN if remote)

# All should successfully access service

Test 7: Monitoring Verification

# Check Prometheus:
http://prometheus.lab.local/targets
# Service should show UP

# Check Grafana:
http://grafana.lab.local
# Navigate to Explore
# Query metrics or logs for service
# Should return data

Test 8: Backup Verification

# Run backup:
cd /opt/ansible/playbooks
ansible-playbook backup-homelab.yml

# Verify backup created:
ssh [user]@[target-vm]
ls -lh /opt/backups/[service]-*
# Should show recent backup with non-zero size

# Verify backup contents:
tar -tzf /opt/backups/[service]-[latest].tar.gz | head
# Should list expected files

Test 9: Restore Verification (Critical Services Only)

# Create test data
# Run backup
# Simulate disaster: docker compose stop [service] && rm -rf /opt/docker/[service]/data/*
# Restore from backup (follow documented procedure)
# Verify test data restored

Test 10: Dependencies Check

# If service depends on database:
docker compose stop postgres # or mariadb
# Service should show error or fail to start
docker compose start postgres
docker compose restart [service]
# Service should recover

Testing Checklist Summary:

[ ] DNS resolves correctly
[ ] Service accessible via hostname
[ ] Basic functionality works
[ ] Data persists after restart
[ ] Container restart successful
[ ] Accessible from multiple clients
[ ] Monitoring collecting data
[ ] Backup creates valid file
[ ] Restore procedure works (critical services)
[ ] Dependencies handled correctly

If any test fails, DO NOT proceed. Fix issue before continuing.

